 MBOMBELA – Moya Phosa was bade farewell by her loved ones yesterday. The 39-year-old mother of two passed away on Monday. The Mpumalanga Youth Choir performed. Programme director Oupa Pilane shared messages of condolences from people unable to attend throughout the service.  READ MORE: Moya Phosa passes away The service was attended by, among others, the former first lady of Mozambique and Nelson Mandela’s widow, Graça Machel, as well as deputy president David Mabuza and Julius Malema, EFF leader.    She will be laid to rest next to her grandmother in the family graveyard in Polen in Limpopo on Saturday. ALSO SEE GALLERY: Big show of support for Phosa family at daughter’s memorial